text: I had a meeting with a couple of
partners today if we could call it that
sitting in my office redlining a
contract due at 6:00 and Stephen walks
in with Jack asks me where my parents
were born oh no I said India because
that's what I could on the form when I
was hired because it technically was
India when my father was born there but
the names of the cities you've listed
are not in India Stephen says they're in
Pakistan well my father was born in 1946
when it was all one country before the
British came along and chopped it up
into two countries in 1947 your mother
was born when 1948 so it wasn't India
anymore it wasn't it was Pakistan I mean
my clock is ticking and wasting time on
a history lesson
turns out Stephen is trying to ascertain
if I have misrepresented myself it was
all India honey so there's a different
name on it now so what he knew about the
name change to your birth name is not
Kapoor Stephen says it's Abdullah why
did you change it I changed my social
when I changed my name it's before I met
you yes it's legal they do it all the
time for identity theft Stephen has been
digging around he's got it in for me I
knew I never should have gone to that
hearing
